---
import StoryImage from '@images/story.png';
---

<div id="story">
  <div class="text">
    <h1>{'Our Story'}</h1>
    <p>
      Workout4Wildlife was born out of a passion for fitness and wildlife
      conservation. In 2022, we went on a bike ride across Namibia, one of the
      most remote places on earth.
    </p>

    <p>
      Blown away by its landscape and wildlife, we challenged ourselves to
      contribute towards the conservation of the beauty we encountered.
    </p>

    <p>
      Upon our return, we founded W4W. Our goal is to leverage the fitness
      community to raise funds for wildlife conservation projects globally.
    </p>
    <h2>Alfredo, Guido, Julian & Lukas</h2>
  </div>
  <img src={StoryImage} alt="Our Story" loading="lazy" />
</div>

<style>
  #story {
    box-sizing: border-box;
    width: 100%;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: var(--padding-side) var(--padding-side);
  }

  h1 {
    text-align: left;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: calc(var(--margin) * 2);
  }

  .text {
    margin-top: var(--margin);
    margin-right: calc(var(--margin) * 2);
    max-width: calc(var(--base-font-size) * 50);
  }

  p {
    margin: var(--margin) 0px;
  }

  img {
    width: 40%;
    max-width: calc(var(--base-font-size) * 25);
    object-fit: scale-down;
  }

  @media only screen and (max-width: 970px) {
    #story {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }

    h1,
    h2 {
      text-align: center;
    }

    h2 {
      margin-bottom: var(--margin);
    }

    .text {
      margin-top: 0px;
      margin-right: 0px;
    }

    p {
      text-align: center;
    }

    img {
      min-width: 292px;
    }
  }
</style>
